## Chat Commands — Workflow Shortcuts

Users can run all workflow scripts using natural language in Claude Code chat. When you see these phrases, run the corresponding Python command:

| User says | What to run |
|---|---|
| `run standup` / `run stand up` | `python workflows/standup.py` |
| `show requirements` / `list requirements` | `python workflows/requirements.py --list` |
| `trace REQ-XXX` | `python workflows/requirements.py --trace REQ-XXX` |
| `run work` / `show work` | `python workflows/work.py --list` |
| `work on REQ-XXX` | `python workflows/work.py --requirement REQ-XXX` |
| `generate report` / `weekly report` | `python workflows/report.py` |
| `run report last week` | `python workflows/report.py --week-offset -1` |
| `show commits` / `what was committed today` | `git log --oneline --since="midnight"` |
| `pause` | Save work session state to `workflows/.session/`, resume later with `work on REQ-XXX` |
| `show open PRs` | `gh pr list` |
| `commit [message]` | Stage relevant changes and commit with the given message |
| `push` / `push to GitHub` | `git push` (confirm with user first) |

